Bring a #large pot{} of water to a boil with a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Meanwhile, peel the @ginger{1%thumb} with a #spoon{}, then mince or grate along with the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced or grated). Thinly slice the @scallions{2}(thinly sliced, white and green parts separated). Trim and discard the root and tops of the @leek{1}, then halve and thinly slice. Rinse under water, tossing, to remove any silt. Drain.

Heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add the @shiitake mushrooms{4%ounce} and cook, tossing, ~{5-6%minutes}, until soft and golden brown. Set aside.

In the same pan, heat @olive oil{1/2%tablespoon} over medium heat. Add the leek to the pan and cook, tossing, ~{4-5%minutes}, until softened. Add the @porcini mushroom powder{1%teaspoon}, scallion whites, ginger, and garlic to the pot and cook, stirring, another ~stirring{30%seconds}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Add @water{5%cups}, @soy sauce{3%tablespoon}, and @veggie stock concentrate{4} to the pot and bring to a simmer for ~{10%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt, if necessary.

Meanwhile, add the @udon noodles{2%bunch} to the boiling water and cook ~{9-10%minutes}, until al dente. Drain and divide between two #bowls{}.

Top the udon with the broth, then arrange the shiitakes and @seaweed{1} along the sides of the bowl. Garnish with scallion greens and enjoy!

> Forget your college dorm ramen. This ramen is the real deal. An umami-packed broth gives this dish intense depth, while meaty shiitakes and briny seaweed add unexpected bursts of flavor. Warning: loud slurping may occur.